data.title: Newcastle Bone Density Centre
data.meta_description: Newcastle Bone Density Centre is a private medical imaging centre in the Newcastle and Hunter Region offering both bone density scanning and body composition scanning.
data.text:
Bone Density Scans

A dual energy x-ray absorptiometry (DEXA) scan is a medical procedure used to measure the density of your bones. The test can assist in determining your risk of fractures. Based on this assessment, anti-osteoporotic treatment could be considered by your doctor.

Find out more

Body Composition Scans

Body Composition Scanning is used to determine the proportions of different tissue types in your body. This technique has been widely used to assess fat and muscle mass. Results can be used to measure changes over time.

Find out more
